        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 11:29AM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 1129 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cobleskill, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cobleskill, Duanesburg, Schoharie, Delanson, Central Bridge,
Carlisle, Esperance, Duane, Lykers, Old Central Bridge, Lawyersville,
Rockwell Corners, Grovenor Corners, Old Stone Fort, Market Corners,
Quaker Street, Little York, Becker Corners, Burtonsville, and Shutts
Corners.

This includes Interstate 88 between exits 22 and 23.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
